Package: review
Title: Tidy Relational Algebra for Semantic Review
Version: 0.0.2
Language: en-GB
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Daniel", 
           family = "Antal", 
           email = "daniel.antal@dataobservatory.eu", 
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-7513-6760"))
Description: Provides a tidy relational algebra for iterative semantic review of
   tabular data. The package provides a vectorised, tidy review workspace for 
   creating, reviewing, explaining, and finalising semantic claims. Rather than
   prescribing how reviews are carried out, it supports reproducible review 
   workflows that remain compatible with ordinary data frames and external 
   tools such as spreadsheets, databases, and interactive review interfaces. 
   Although it is not an ontology toolkit, its design is informed by 
   provenance, policy, and statistical quality-control models, allowing review 
   histories to be audited, serialised, and compared with explicit 
   review expectations.
